                        },
                        "displayName": "Ben Kietzman",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "In addition to removing io::FileSystem and io::FileStatistics, should HdfsPathInfo be replaced with fs::FileStats? It carries more information than fs::FileStats: last access time in addition to last modified time (though in seconds rather than ns since the epoch), block size, replication, and permissions. io-hdfs.pxi passes all of this for {{some_hdfs.ls(some_path, detail=True)}} but the docstring does not provide specifics about what metadata is guaranteed and test_hdfs.py doesn't even call {{ls(... detail=True)}}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
